      • evaluate

        IExtendedIterator<R> evaluate()
        Evaluates the query and returns an iterator over the results. Depending on the type of query the returned iterator is usually either a
        • ITupleResult for SELECT queries with elements of type IBindings
        • IGraphResult for CONSTRUCT queries with elements of type IStatement or
        • IBooleanResult for ASK queries with one element of type Boolean
        The element types of the returned iterators can be changed by using the methods bindResultType(Class, Class...) or restrictResultType(Class, Class...). This makes it possible to return the type Object[] for ITupleResults or to map ITupleResults with one projection variable or IGraphResult directly to mapped beans.
        Returns:
        Iterator over the results of the query.

      • evaluate

        <T> IExtendedIterator<T> evaluate(Class<T> resultType,
                                  Class<?>... resultTypes)
        Evaluates the query and returns an iterator over the results while asserting some specific types of the result elements. This method is a shorthand for using bindResultType(Class, Class...) and then evaluate(). If the given resultTypes are mapped bean interfaces then it is guaranteed that the returned beans implement at least those interfaces. The related rdf:type statements don't have to be contained within the RDF store. Other possible resultTypes include IBindings or Object[] for SELECT queries, IStatement for construct queries or Boolean for ASK queries.
        Returns:
        Iterator over the results of the query.
        See Also:
        bindResultType(Class, Class...)

      • evaluateRestricted

        <T> IExtendedIterator<T> evaluateRestricted(Class<T> resultType,
                                            Class<?>... resultTypes)
        Evaluates the query and returns an iterator over the results while asserting some specific types of the result elements without touching the RDF store for type information. This method is a shorthand for using restrictResultType(Class, Class...) and then evaluate().
        Returns:
        Iterator over the results of the query.
        See Also:
        restrictResultType(Class, Class...)

      • bindResultType

        <T> IQuery<T> bindResultType(Class<T> resultType,
                             Class<?>... resultTypes)

      • restrictResultType

        <T> IQuery<T> restrictResultType(Class<T> resultType,
                                 Class<?>... resultTypes)
        Restricts the types of the result values to the given resultTypes. This ensures that no additional queries are executed to retrieve the actual types of the values.
        Parameters:
        resultTypes - The types for the result values
        Returns:
        The query object
